21/12/2005
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Serbia-Montenegro -- UNMIK announced on Tuesday (20 December) that it has authorised the establishment of justice and interior ministries in the province.
Jean Dussourd, the UN's special representative for police and justice, said the decision highlighted the international community's confidence in the ability of Kosovo to manage its own affairs.
Prime Minister Bajram Kosumi welcomed the move as one that would strengthen Kosovo's image as a democratic entity in Europe.
In other news, US troops serving in Kosovo visited the province's biggest orphanage on Tuesday to present Christmas gifts to children there.
Money for the presents was collected from the 1,800 US soldiers in Kosovo.
(AP, DPA - 20/12/05)
